          <h3>After the operation</h3>
          <p class="fst-italic">
            After donating blood, you will be seated in an observation unit where you can relax and have a snack. After
            15 minutes have passed, you can leave. After donating blood:<br>

            Make sure to drink plenty of fluids.<br>
            Avoid strenuous physical activity or heavy lifting for about five hours.<br>
            If you feel dizzy, lie down with your feet up until the feeling goes away.<br>
            Keep the bandage dry and in place for five hours.<br>
            If you bleed after removing the bandage, apply pressure to the bleeding site and raise your arm until it
            stops.<br>
            In the event of a bruise, apply cold compresses to the area from time to time during the first 24 hours.<br>
            And try to add iron-rich foods to your diet to replace iron lost from donating blood.<br>
          </p>
          <p>
            Contact the blood donation center or the doctor in the following cases:<br>

            If you forgot to inform the Blood Donation Center of any important health information.<br>
            If you develop signs and symptoms associated with an illness, such as a fever, within several days after
            donating blood.<br>
            If you are diagnosed with COVID-19 within 48 hours after donating blood.<br>
          </p>
